 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Beast Mastery Hunter Phase 5 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 160 top-ranked Beast Mastery Hunter DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 5 (Sunwell Plateau), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Beast Mastery Hunter items in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Gronnstalker's Bracers (95%), Gronnstalker's Belt (95%), Gronnstalker's Boots (95%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Sunwell Plateau."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Beast Mastery Hunter use in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Bold Crimson Spinel, Wicked Pyrestone and Great Lionseye in the coloured sockets. Phase 5 is where the epic gems from Sunwell replace their rare equivalents — that swap alone is worth several item levels across a full set."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Beast Mastery Hunter need in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Might of the Scourge on shoulders, Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Greater Agility on weapon. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
